The paper presents a distributed algorithm for finding Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) in the Congested Clique model, which is a well-studied topic in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The algorithm also involves techniques related to graph theory and algorithms, such as Connected Components and sparsification, which suggest the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity). The communication model used in the algorithm involves limited edge bandwidth, which falls under the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper also mentions other graph problems that can be solved using the same technique, which relates to the sub-category cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
